ContentDesc_Das südliche Kreszentia: Even the most dauntless of sailors would sooner abandon ship than steer into Shades' Triangle. Fooled by the lush and fertile island shimmering on the horizon─men and vessels alike have been lost to its allure, never to be seen again. Yet this fearsome reputation has done little to quell Ketenramm's appetite for adventure. Having joined his intrepid crew, you venture forth unto the high seas, only to be confounded by a shifting mirage. Amidst the confusion, a strange voice beckons you onward as the vessel is inexorably drawn towards the crescent-shaped isle. What secrets await upon its southern shores?
FATEs_Kill Boss_A Delicate Balance_Desc: While the fiery familiars of the island are tasked with regulating the temperatures of their surroundings, there are times when they become overzealous in their duties. Their flames must be extinguished ere they give rise to an inferno.
FATEs_Kill Boss_A Prying Eye_Desc: What better to keep watch over the natural balance of things than an ahriman? Its eye sees all, and now it spies adventurers who threaten to trample upon the carefully maintained order.
FATEs_Kill Boss_An Unending Duty_Desc: Deep within crystalline caves, a great stone beast has awoken from its slumber. Wreathed in lightning, it dispenses divine judgment upon any who would stand before it.
FATEs_Kill Boss_Brain Drain_Desc: The potent toxins within this creature's body turn living organisms into mindless servants, bound to their master's whims. It must be dealt with before the entire island falls under its thrall.
FATEs_Kill Boss_Fatal Allure_Desc: With fiery magicks, this winged creature renders its final verdict upon the living, draining their vital energy for its own. While its eerie beauty and deadly grace are enchanting to behold, it cannot be allowed to roam free.
FATEs_Kill Boss_King of the Crescent_Des: All the beasts and familiars of the Occult Crescent fear the Ropross, its presence marked ever by the final screams of its victims. What group of brave explorers will end its reign of terror once and for all?
FATEs_Kill Boss_Rough Waters_Desc: With the ocean waves at its beck and call, Nammu has long been the scourge of sailors in the region. Its extermination would do much to ensure safer trade routes and calm waters.
FATEs_Kill Boss_Serving Darkness_Desc: Lifereaper strikes at the living, hoarding their aether to sate the hunger of its gluttonous kin. This dark harvest can be suffered no longer.
FATEs_Kill Boss_Sworn to Soil_Desc: The soil of the Occult Crescent must be carefully managed, and this pungent familiar has been tasked with the job. Anyone who gets in the way of its dirty work will face the full fury of the earth.
FATEs_Kill Boss_The Golden Guardian_Desc: Engraved with runes of ancient power, the gilded headstone has come to life to drive away the intruders. Only by reducing it to rubble can safe passage be secured.
FATEs_Kill Boss_The Winged Terror_Desc: Every sailor in the Indigo Deep keeps watch for the massive bird which stalks the skies overhead. It has made a meal of more than one hapless crew─yet occasionally, even the deadliest predators bite off more than they can chew.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Persistent Pots_: A group of magic pots has earned the ire of the island's beasts with their incessant pleas for elixirs. The beleaguered things appear to be in dire need of rescue...surely they'll have learned their lesson after this.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Pleading Pots_De: It seems the magic pots are loath to learn from their mistakes, as they have once again followed their greed for elixirs into trouble. The pitiful creatures must be saved from their own folly...but perhaps not immediately.
